  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This first guy, I'll never forget.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, once, I wrote an essay in-- in college in Canada when I came over here.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I always-- I-- the title, I wrote a story that was called, 'The German Army in Victory and Defeat.' And in victory, he was my symbol because he was absolutely a strapping man, very heavy set, clean shaven, uniform, still see it, like brand new.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Boots, everything shiny.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His motorcycle just came out of a factory.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then he-- and then they-- they kind of-- As a matter of fact, before-- just before they caught up with us, they were also bombing the roads with-- with-- with fire bombs.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then we had to-- we had to dive into the fields and into the ditches because we were all mixed up with the Allied troops, you see.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we were-- the first time I was really fired upon in my life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after they caught up with us, we couldn't just continue.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then we had to make an about-turn, and  we all returned to where we came from, except for a handful of people who be able to trickle out of the ranks and disappear.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was the first big change-- an exodus and a return to a totally different lifestyle.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was May--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "May 1940.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- looking for ages-- I was nine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My brother was five.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From there on, things started to change because the Germans had a program where they gradually started to intimidate, isolate, and-- and organize the Jewish community for deportation.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
